**Elzhan stood facing Sans, his eyes locked onto the grinning skeleton in front of him. This was it, the moment he had been waiting for. He had heard tales of Sans' incredible power and his ability to dodge even the most powerful attacks. But Elzhan was determined to come out on top. With a determined look on his face, Elzhan raised his hands and summoned a barrage of magic missiles, which flew at Sans with lightning speed. To his surprise, however, Sans dodged every single one with ease, his grin never faltering. Elzhan gritted his teeth and charged at Sans, his fists clenched. Sans merely sidestepped him, his body phasing through Elzhan's as if he wasn't even there. Elzhan stumbled and turned around, only to be met with a bone attack that sent him flying across the room. As Elzhan picked himself up, he realized that Sans was not going to be an easy opponent to defeat. But he was determined to keep going, to keep fighting until he emerged victorious. He took a deep breath and charged at Sans once more, this time with a renewed determination in his heart. He dodged Sans' attacks with surprising agility, his own strikes hitting their mark. The battle raged on for what felt like hours, each combatant giving it their all. In the end, it was Elzhan who emerged victorious. He stood over the fallen skeleton, his chest heaving with exertion. As he looked down at his defeated foe, he couldn't help but feel a sense of respect for Sans and his incredible abilities. And as he walked away from the battle, Elzhan couldn't help but wonder what other challenges lay ahead for him, what other opponents he would have to face and overcome. But for now, he was content in the knowledge that he had faced one of the greatest challenges of his life and emerged victorious. --uplight --v 4** - Upscaled by <@1079071413593452544> (fast)
